RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 86. Allowance Purse 32000. FOR MN-BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR TRIAL OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OUT RUN'M saved ground around the first turn, chased the leader up the backstretch, began a bid from the two path coming around the far turn and drew off in the stretch. MYSTIFIER raced at the back of the pack on the inside through the opening half mile, continued to save ground around the second bend, began a bid in upper stretch and gained ground late. NORTH ARM BAY raced in the two path early, trailed the field on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the far bend in the three path and improved position in the lane. UNDERTOW led the way from the two path around the first turn and up the backstretch, came around the far turn still in the two path and faded in the stretch. HARMON KILLER BREW raced in the two path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch off the pace on the inside, saved ground around the second bend and was empty in the lane while drifting out in the final furlong. MIDNIGHT ROYAL raced in the three path around the first bend, settled off the pace on the outside for the run up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the two path and made no bid.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 2 5F Turf CR: 68. Claiming Purse 14000. RACE.FOOTNOTES: SAVONA led the field up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn, kicked clear entering the stretch and held off a closer to the wire. RIGHT OF REFUSAL stalked the leader on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, came around the bend in the two path, challenged approaching the quarter pole and dueled in the lane but could not get by the winner. THORN CROWN chased the pace setter on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn, raced into traffic and checked sharply nearing the quarter pole and gained ground in late stretch. CHAPARRITA raced off the pace on the outside early, navigated the far turn from the four path and improved position mildly while never threatening. PURRFECT MOON tracked the leader between horses through the opening stages, raced in the three path around the turn and was outkicked in the stretch. IZE SHARPIE raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, dropped back to trail the field while saving ground around the bend and was empty from there.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 3 1M Dirt CR: 65. Claiming Purse 10500. MORE ROMANCE raced in the three path early, tracked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, continued around the far turn in the two path and kept on to the finish. ICYWILBURNYEH raced off the pace in the two path through the opening half mile, saved ground around the far bend and improved position mildly in the stretch. PICAFLOR hit the gate leaving it, raced in the two path around the first turn, chased the leader between horses up the backstretch, saved ground around the far turn, led in upper stretch and flattened out in the final furlong. ALQWANI saved ground early, led the way on the inside up the backstretch, floated out to the three path coming off the far bend and tired from there.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: DREAMING BIZ saved ground around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack on the outside for the run up the backstretch, began a bid from the five path coming around the second turn, dueled in the lane and got up for the win late. RENTAL POOL raced in the two path around the first turn, tracked the leader on the inside up the backstretch, started a bid from the three path coming around the far turn, dueled in the stretch and narrowly missed. FAT AND FURIOUS saved ground around the first turn, raced off the pace up the backstretch, continued around the second turn in the four path, launched a bid passing the quarter pole and gained ground late from there. SHES GOT THE POWER saved ground early, raced in the middle of the pack on the inside up the backstretch, swung out to the four path to began a bid coming off the far turn and improved position in the lane. SHE B GLAMOROUS raced at the back of the pack in the two path through the opening half mile, continued around the far turn in the five path and passed tiring horses in the stretch. LILA'S LUCKY LADY angled in to save ground around the first turn, chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, navigated the far bend from the two path and was outkicked in the final furlong. BID FOR POWER raced in the two path around the first turn, tracked the leader between horses up the backstretch, dueled around the second turn still in the two path and weakened in the stretch. SILVERA trailed the field from the two path around the first turn and up the backstretch, saved ground around the far bend and never threatened. SASSY CAT saved ground around the first turn, led the way up the backstretch, dueled from the rail around the second turn and tired in the lane. MIZZANNA raced in the three path early, stalked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, dropped back while shifting out to the six path coming off the far turn and continued to faded from there.
